<DATELINE>COOKE CITY, Mont. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Fire trucks from as far away as <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION> took position in two smoke-filled <LOCATION> Montana </LOCATION> towns Monday and residents here waited to see if a backfire would burn fast enough to protect them from a wind-driven forest fire. `` First it starts snowing ash. Then it starts raining fire,'' said fire information officer <PERSON> Pat </PERSON> <PERSON> Kaunert </PERSON> as he stood in a 65-foot-wide fire break bulldozed through the forest. Top federal officials said that blaze and 12 other fires in and around <ORGANIZATION> Yellowstone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Park </ORGANIZATION> had burned 900,000 acres as of Monday. <PERSON> Gary </PERSON> <PERSON> Cargill </PERSON>, chief federal forester for the <LOCATION> Rocky </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mountains </LOCATION>, warned that an additional 300,000 acres may be consumed this week, despite the efforts of 9,000 firefighters. And <ORGANIZATION> Cargill </ORGANIZATION> warned that 20 to 30 mph southwesterly wind is expected to arrive in the region Tuesday with a weather front. Protection of life and property are the top priorities, he said at a news conference in <LOCATION> Bozeman </LOCATION>. `` Containment of further acreage is just not in the cards.'' He said many of the nation's best firefighters `` are being whipped day after day'' by the Yellowstone fires. Evacuation orders for <ORGANIZATION> Cooke </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> and a town three miles west, <LOCATION> Silver </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gate </LOCATION>, were issued Sunday morning. By Monday night, about 30 of the approximately 150 residents in the two towns remained, said <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Fry </PERSON>, an emergency services official. `` Some of them are staying around because they want to see what the fire does,'' Fry said. `` They're mostly packed up, though, and we're trying to push them out.'' A backfire had been set by firefighters as a shi