<DATELINE>BOISE, Idaho (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 With 25,000 firefighters in the West, the logistics of supplying all of them is staggering, say officials of the federal center established to do just that. As of Monday, the <ORGANIZATION> Boise </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Interagency </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> has sent out 50,000 pairs of fire retardant gloves, 25,445 pairs of flame-proof trousers and nearly 32,000 paper sleeping bags. It also has distributed 41,607 canteens, 30,984 shirts, nearly 3,000 cans of foot powder, 15 pocket dictionaries, and for firefighters' internal blazes, 182 bottles of antacid. The center, established in 1965, is responsible for dispatching firefighters, aircraft and supplies to state and federal agencies throughout the country. More than 67,000 fires, burning a record of more than 3.6 million acres, have been reported in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> this year. The previous record was 3.2 million acres in 1985. `` This has been a very long fire season,'' said <PERSON> Arnold </PERSON> <PERSON> Hartigan </PERSON>, public affairs officer. `` It began early in June and now, almost three months later, it shows no signs of letting up.'' Labor Day was typical of the workload. While about 10 people might be on duty on a normal Labor Day, <PERSON> Hartigan </PERSON> said about 150 were working at center this year. The fire management center is made up of personnel from the <ORGANIZATION> Bureau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Land </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Management </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Forest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Park </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Bureau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Indian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Affairs </ORGANIZATION> and the <LOCATION> U.S </LOCATION>. Fish and <ORGANIZATION> Wildlife </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION>. Through the weekend, the center has sent out 2.3 million pounds of supplies, valued at about $ 14 million. Along with the other necessities, <PERSON> Hartigan </PERSON> said, 103,000 message forms have been distributed to firefighters. `` This is ... the government, and we do need to keep up on our paperwork,'' he said.
