<HEAD>Zoo Closes Exhibit To Help Homesick Panda</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Cincinnati </LOCATION> Zoo officials are giving giant panda <LOCATION> Chia </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Chia </LOCATION> five days off to see if he can overcome what they believe is homesickness. <PERSON> Chia </PERSON> <PERSON> Chia </PERSON> went on display Friday at the start of a three-month stopover on his move from the <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> Zoo to <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>. But the zoo administrators closed the exhibit the same day because the panda was staying in his den and acting strangely. `` At first, we thought it was jet lag, but it's taken much longer than we expected,'' said <PERSON> Jo </PERSON> <PERSON> Gipps </PERSON>, curator of mammals with the <ORGANIZATION> London </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Zoo </ORGANIZATION>, who traveled with <PERSON> Chia </PERSON> <PERSON> Chia </PERSON>. `` Homesick is exactly the word for what's wrong.'' Since Friday, the 290-pound panda has emerged periodically from his den to eat bamboo for a few minutes, then quickly retreated from public view. When keepers tried to lock the doors to his den to keep him in view, the panda became agitated, pacing rapidly and bumping the walls. `` He's normally quite extroverted. That's why we're concerned,'' said <PERSON> Neil </PERSON> <PERSON> Bemment </PERSON>, the panda's keeper. `` Animals are unpredictable. We're not going to push him,'' said <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Maruska </PERSON>, executive director of the <ORGANIZATION> Cincinnati </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Zoo </ORGANIZATION>. He and officials from the <ORGANIZATION> London </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Zoo </ORGANIZATION> decided <PERSON> Chia </PERSON> <PERSON> Chia </PERSON> needed time alone in his new surroundings. Zoo officials will meet Thursday to decide if the exhibit can reopen Friday. Zookeepers built a platform for the panda Monday to make him feel like he is at his old <ORGANIZATION> London </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Zoo </ORGANIZATION> home