<HEAD>Food, Water Poisoning Kill Three Lebanese, Fell 150 Others</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Food and water poisoning killed three people and hospitalized more than 150 in two separate incidents, police said Tuesday. They said 53 victims were poisoned by eating meat sandwiches late Monday at a restaurant in the northern port of <LOCATION> Tripoli </LOCATION>. `` Most of the 53 ... came in screaming from severe stomach aches,'' said a nurse at a <LOCATION> Tripoli </LOCATION> hospital. `` Later they started fainting and than three died. There was nothing we could do,'' she added, refusing to give her name. The owner of the restaurant on <LOCATION> Tripoli </LOCATION>'s fashionable <PERSON> Azmi </PERSON> <PERSON> Street </PERSON> was arrested. In south <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION>, more than 100 people were hospitalized Tuesday after drinking from an artesian well in the village of <LOCATION> Rzai </LOCATION>, 15 miles northeast of the ancient port city of Tyre, police reported. `` The poisoning is due to an overdose of chlorine used to purify the well's water,'' said Dr. <PERSON> Raymond </PERSON> <PERSON> Saarour </PERSON> at Tyre's government hospital. Sources at the <ORGANIZATION> Health </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Beirut </LOCATION> said medical and other supplies would be sent to Tyre to help cope with the emergency.
