ng, when all fire and police personnel would have been laid off, garbage collection would end and the city would cease to function. The mayor said that although formal cuts had not begun, 25 percent of <LOCATION> Yonkers </LOCATION>' scheduled garbage pickups were canceled Tuesday because of a lack of diesel fuel as the city limits fuel purchases. `` The garbage is piling up today, the libraries will be closed next week,'' the mayor said. `` It may take deep cuts in city services to get the people of <LOCATION> Yonkers </LOCATION> to tell their councilmen that they want this matter settled.''
