r married and left some of his millions to his partner and nephew, <PERSON> Perry </PERSON> <PERSON> Bass </PERSON>. <PERSON> Perry </PERSON>'s four sons each inherited $ 2.8 million, and they combined assets to form <ORGANIZATION> Bass </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brothers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Enterprises </ORGANIZATION>, which built up the family wealth through shrewd investments. In 1968, <PERSON> Perry </PERSON>, a competitive sailor, handed over the business to son <PERSON> Sid </PERSON>. All educated at <ORGANIZATION> Yale </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION>, the Bass brothers have been described as atypical <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> tycoons with a conservative style and quiet manner. After starting his business career with <ORGANIZATION> Wells </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fargo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Bass </PERSON> returned to <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> in 1974 to a spot at <ORGANIZATION> Bass </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brothers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Enterprises </ORGANIZATION>. Tales of rivalries among the four brothers surfaced in recent years, and in 1983 <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> broke away and formed <ORGANIZATION> Robert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> M. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bass </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> to pursue deals on his own. The savings and loan deal announced Monday is just the latest in a series for Bass in recent months. He bought the <ORGANIZATION> Westin </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hotel </ORGANIZATION> chain from <ORGANIZATION> Allegis </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> for $ 1.53 billion, then in March sold the Plaza Hotel in <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION> for $ 410 million to developer <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Trump </PERSON>. On May 17, <PERSON> Bass </PERSON> reached an agreement to pay $ 702 million to acquire <ORGANIZATION> Be